WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.740 --> 00:00:09.630
hi I'm Todd from Sony and I'm going to
take you through the steps for setting

00:00:09.630 --> 00:00:14.289
up your sony Blu-Ray disc player to
connect to your wireless network

00:00:14.289 --> 00:00:19.650
which features this type of menu system

00:00:19.650 --> 00:00:23.680
your Sony Blu-Ray disc player has the
capability to connect to your

00:00:23.680 --> 00:00:25.929
wireless network and internet

00:00:25.929 --> 00:00:32.929
this allows you to stream a wide variety
of movies tv episodes music videos

00:00:32.929 --> 00:00:35.400
live sports events and more

00:00:35.400 --> 00:00:39.720
for my demonstration I'm using
the BDP-S580

00:00:39.720 --> 00:00:43.940
and a KDL-32BX310

00:00:43.940 --> 00:00:45.840
products can be slightly different

00:00:45.840 --> 00:00:50.420
so be sure to check the owner's manual
or visit us at esupport.Sony.com

00:00:51.440 --> 00:00:55.000
for your specific features and menu options

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:56.490
you will need to ensure

00:00:56.490 --> 00:00:59.679
that your Blu-Ray disc player
is connected to your tv

00:00:59.679 --> 00:01:04.879
and you are able to view the menu of
the Blu-Ray disc player on the tv

00:01:04.879 --> 00:01:09.040
if you have not done this yet you can
find the steps to make this connection

00:01:09.040 --> 00:01:11.030
with the quickstart guide

00:01:11.030 --> 00:01:13.010
owners manual

00:01:13.010 --> 00:01:18.150
or visit esupport.Sony.com 
for specific directions

00:01:18.150 --> 00:01:23.630
to get started you will need to turn on
your tv and your Blu-Ray disc player

00:01:23.630 --> 00:01:25.799
make sure you select the proper input

00:01:25.799 --> 00:01:28.690
that your blu ray disc player is connected to

00:01:28.690 --> 00:01:36.090
for my example I'm connected to HDMI 2

00:01:36.090 --> 00:01:39.340
using the remote for your Sony Blu-Ray disc player

00:01:39.340 --> 00:01:42.120
press the Home button

00:01:42.120 --> 00:01:44.530
using the remote arrow keys

00:01:44.530 --> 00:01:46.300
scroll to the far left

00:01:46.300 --> 00:01:49.340
to the Setup icon

00:01:49.340 --> 00:01:54.350
using the remote arrow keys scroll down
to Network Settings

00:01:54.350 --> 00:01:56.920
press Enter

00:01:56.920 --> 00:01:59.870
highlight Internet Settings

00:01:59.870 --> 00:02:02.250
press Enter

00:02:02.250 --> 00:02:07.520
highlight Wireless Setup
press Enter

00:02:07.520 --> 00:02:09.889
highlight Scan

00:02:09.889 --> 00:02:12.539
and press Enter

00:02:12.539 --> 00:02:14.799
you will see a screen showing

00:02:14.799 --> 00:02:18.719
Searching for available wireless networks

00:02:18.719 --> 00:02:23.459
your Blu-Ray disc player is looking for
all wireless connections within your range

00:02:26.199 --> 00:02:30.339
this screen shows a list of available
wireless connections

00:02:30.339 --> 00:02:33.379
highlight your network

00:02:33.379 --> 00:02:35.609
press Enter

00:02:35.609 --> 00:02:38.199
if you have a password on your network

00:02:38.199 --> 00:02:42.239
you'll need to enter it at this point

00:02:42.239 --> 00:02:46.739
you will now see a screen that shows
Please select how to set up the IP address

00:02:46.739 --> 00:02:54.669
and proxy server settings of the unit
highlight Auto

00:02:54.669 --> 00:02:56.809
press Enter

00:02:56.809 --> 00:02:58.569
you'll see a screen

00:02:58.569 --> 00:03:01.799
that shows you how your network is configured

00:03:01.799 --> 00:03:04.809
this is just an overview of your network

00:03:04.809 --> 00:03:09.149
you do not need to take any action at this screen

00:03:09.149 --> 00:03:13.869
use the right arrow key to continue

00:03:13.869 --> 00:03:16.149
you'll see a screen that shows

00:03:16.149 --> 00:03:18.329
To establish a connection

00:03:18.329 --> 00:03:21.879
select Save &amp; Connect

00:03:21.879 --> 00:03:25.319
highlight Save &amp; Connect

00:03:25.319 --> 00:03:27.939
press Enter

00:03:27.939 --> 00:03:29.829
you'll see the message

00:03:29.829 --> 00:03:35.089
Connecting to the network Please wait

00:03:35.089 --> 00:03:38.749
the connection to your wireless network
is now complete

00:03:38.749 --> 00:03:43.699
and you can see the confirmation that
you're connected on the screen

00:03:43.699 --> 00:03:45.659
OK is highlighted

00:03:45.659 --> 00:03:47.529
press Enter

00:03:47.529 --> 00:03:50.859
we are now back at our home menu

00:03:50.859 --> 00:03:52.219
we're connected

00:03:52.219 --> 00:03:54.629
so let's go to the internet

00:03:54.629 --> 00:03:56.859
using your left arrow key

00:03:56.859 --> 00:03:59.719
go back to Network Settings

00:03:59.719 --> 00:04:01.409
use the right arrow key

00:04:01.409 --> 00:04:03.519
to go to Network

00:04:03.519 --> 00:04:05.589
highlight Internet Browser

00:04:05.589 --> 00:04:08.709
and press Enter

00:04:08.709 --> 00:04:11.689
press the Options button on the remote

00:04:11.689 --> 00:04:15.589
and the browser setup is displayed

00:04:15.589 --> 00:04:18.109
highlight URL entry

00:04:18.109 --> 00:04:19.810
and press Enter

00:04:19.810 --> 00:04:26.499
this displays a software keyboard which
allows you to type in a web site address

00:04:26.499 --> 00:04:28.339
for our example

00:04:28.339 --> 00:04:33.099
we're going to type in Sony.com

00:04:33.099 --> 00:04:34.339
use the arrow key

00:04:34.339 --> 00:04:36.849
to select each letter

00:04:36.849 --> 00:04:38.580
once a letter is highlighted

00:04:38.580 --> 00:04:40.300
press Enter

00:04:40.300 --> 00:04:43.830
once you have spelled out the complete
website address

00:04:43.830 --> 00:04:47.439
press the green Enter button on the remote

00:04:47.439 --> 00:04:49.100
you can use the arrow keys

00:04:49.100 --> 00:04:53.190
to move around the web page

00:04:53.190 --> 00:04:58.710
for more tips tricks and how-to videos
please visit us at esupport.Sony.com

00:04:59.719 --> 00:05:03.869
or on our SonyListens youtube channel

00:05:03.869 --> 00:05:04.219
thank you

